cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on using wearable sensors to detect stereotypical motor movements in individuals with Autism Spectrum Disorders. The use of deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks and long short-term memory networks, is central to the proposed method. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of parameter transfer learning and ensemble learning suggests that Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) may also be relevant sub-categories.
